               <note>The church is situated in the town Lālibalā and is part of the south-eastern cluster of churches.
                  Though hewn in the rock, it presents features that are indebted to Aksumite architecture.
                It is believed that it replicates in some manner the feature of the now-lost Cathedral of Mary of Zion in Aksum.</note>
